T1  - Firm Characteristics and Empirical Factor Models: A Model Mining Experiment
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa126
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 12
SP  - 6087
EP  - 6125
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In a novel model mining experiment, we data mine hundreds of randomly constructed three-factor models and find that many outperform well-known models from the literature, including those with four and five factors. The results provide compelling evidence that the threshold of factor model success needs to be raised. Confidence intervals for model rankings, derived from a bootstrap simulation, offer new insights into the consistency of a model’s pricing ability. Rankings for some well-known models are unusually volatile, which have wider confidence intervals than that of most of the random factor models.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa126
ER  - 



