TY  - JOUR
AU  - Isakov, Dušan
AU  - Pérignon, Christophe
AU  - Weisskopf, Jean-Philippe
T1  - What If Dividends Were Tax-Exempt? Evidence from a Natural Experiment
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab010
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 12
SP  - 5756
EP  - 5795
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study the effect of dividend taxes on the payout and investment policies of publicly listed firms. We exploit a unique setting in Switzerland where, following the corporate tax reform of 2011, some but not all firms were suddenly able to pay tax-exempt dividends. We show that treated firms increase their dividend payout by around 30$\%$ after the tax cut. The effect on payout is less pronounced for firms prone to agency conflicts. We find a significant positive abnormal stock return after the announcement of the payment of a tax-exempt dividend. However, reducing dividend taxes does not boost investment.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab010
ER  - 



